The Biden-Harris Administration has taken significant action to address gun violence and make communities safer. They secured the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act, which expands background checks and funds crisis intervention programs. The legislation also invests in violence prevention programs and addresses youth mental health. The administration is also cracking down on ghost guns, rogue dealers, and gun trafficking. They are committed to investing in community policing, violence intervention, and crime prevention. President Biden signed an Executive Order to advance accountable policing and strengthen public safety. The Safer America Plan funds community policing and promotes effective prosecution of crimes. The Budget aims to prevent and reduce crime, improve the criminal justice system, combat gun violence, support law enforcement, and enforce civil rights. The administration believes more can be done to save lives and improve public safety.